<p><i><b>Dr. Seuss' Horton Hears a Who!</b></i> is a 2008 American <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_Animation" title="Computer Animation" class="mw-redirect">computer-animated</a> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adventure_film" title="Adventure film">adventure</a> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comedy_film" title="Comedy film">comedy</a> film based on the <a href="Dr-2.html" title="Dr. Seuss">Dr. Seuss</a>' <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horton_Hears_a_Who!" title="Horton Hears a Who!">book of the same name</a>. The film was directed by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimmy_Hayward" title="Jimmy Hayward">Jimmy Hayward</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Martino" title="Steve Martino">Steve Martino</a>, and was produced by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blue_Sky_Studios" title="Blue Sky Studios">Blue Sky Studios</a>. It features the voices of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jim_Carrey" title="Jim Carrey">Jim Carrey</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Carell" title="Steve Carell">Steve Carell</a>. Released on March 14, 2008 by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/20th_Century_Fox" title="20th Century Fox">20th Century Fox</a>, it received generally positive reviews, and grossed $297 million on a budget of $85 million.</p>
<p>The film is the third Dr. Seuss feature film adaptation, the second Dr. Seuss film starring <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jim_Carrey" title="Jim Carrey">Jim Carrey</a> after <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dr._Seuss%27_How_the_Grinch_Stole_Christmas_(film)" title="Dr. Seuss' How the Grinch Stole Christmas (film)">How the Grinch Stole Christmas</a></i>, and the first adaptation of a Dr. Seuss work fully animated using <a href="Computer-generated_imagery.html" title="Computer-generated imagery">CGI</a> technology.</p>
<p></p>
